      • getAvailabilityInfo

        ProductModelAvailabilityInfo getAvailabilityInfo(com.guidewire.pc.domain.productmodel.CovTermAvailabilityContext ctx,
                                                 PolicyLinePattern policyLinePattern,
                                                 Offering offering)
        Returns an object that encapuslates availability info for this product given the lookupRoot and other parameter. This method is used when we don't have the coverable entity itself, eg. api call. It provides the ability to query the product model statically.
        Parameters:
        ctx - availability context for this cov term
        policyLinePattern - policy line pattern to check availability for
        offering - a specific offering to check availability for
        Returns:
        a ProductModelAvailabilityInfo object that encapuslates availability info for this product given the lookupRoot and other parameter
